{{Unreferenced|date=September 2008}}
'''Gaussian broadening''' refers to broadening effects in [[spectral line]]s, these can be produced by [[Doppler broadening]] and [[natural broadening]].

This effect is similar to [[Gaussian blur]] effect in [[image processing]] produced by [[convolution]] with the [[Gaussian function]].

The term is named after [[Carl Friedrich Gauss]].

