This hook enables a project to-do list or other similar list to be easily integrated into a project banner. It should be attached to the {{para|HOOK_BOTTOM}} hook.

There are two main parameters, {{para|TODO_LINK}} and {{para|TODO_TEXT}}. Only one should be used at any time. If the todo list is located on a different page then <tt>TODO_LINK</tt> should be used. However, if you've just got some text to include then you can use the <tt>TODO_TEXT</tt> option instead.

If you are using <tt>TODO_LINK</tt> and don't want to see the edit links at the top of the textbox, set <tt>TODO_EDITLINKS=no</tt>.

;Example

{|style="background:none" width="50%"
|<pre style="font-size:85%">
{{WPBannerMeta
|PROJECT          = Tulips
 |small  = {{{small|}}}
 |category={{{category|¬}}}
 |listas = {{{listas|}}}
|NAME             = The Tulip taskforce
|IMAGE_LEFT       = Tulip - floriade canberra.jpg
|HOOK_BOTTOM      = {{WPBannerMeta/hooks/todolist
  |TODO_TITLE = WikiProject Tulips To-do
  |TODO_LINK  = Template:Todo/to do
 }}
}}</pre>
|}
:Produces:
{{WPBannerMeta
|PROJECT          = Tulips
 |small  = {{{small|}}}
 |category=no
 |listas = {{{listas|}}}
|NAME             = The Tulip taskforce
|IMAGE_LEFT       = Tulip - floriade canberra.jpg
|IMAGE_LEFT_LARGE = 50px
|HOOK_BOTTOM      = {{WPBannerMeta/hooks/todolist
  |TODO_TITLE = WikiProject Tulips To-do
  |TODO_LINK  = Template:Todo/to do
 }}
}}

